# Stage Rendering

## Background colour

`#stage` must use `background: var(--vx-blue-ink)` — **never white**.

The stage is scaled via `transform: scale(k)` in `scaleStage()`. At fractional scale
factors, sub-pixel rounding leaves a 1px gap at the slide edges. If `#stage` is white,
that gap bleeds through as a visible white line on dark (`.ink`/`.dark`) slides.

Individual light slides declare their own `background: var(--vx-white)` on `.slide`,
so they are unaffected by the dark stage background.

```css
/* ✅ CORRECT */
#stage { background: var(--vx-blue-ink); }

/* ❌ WRONG — causes white line on dark slides */
#stage { background: var(--vx-white); }
```

## PowerShell git commits

Use semicolons, not `&&`, as statement separators in PowerShell. Pass commit messages
via a variable:

```powershell
$msg = "your commit message here"
git commit -m $msg
```
